def text_lower(text):
    words = [word.lower() for word in text]
    return words

#############################################
def clean_tweet(text):
    text = re.sub('http[s]?://(?:[a-zA-Z]|[0-9]|[$-_@.&+]|[!*\(\),]|(?:%[0-9a-fA-F][0-9a-fA-F]))+', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub('[\n\r\t]', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub('#\w+', '', text)
    text = re.sub('@\w+', '', text)

    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
        u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
        u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
        u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
        u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    
    text = emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

     
    words = text.split(" ")
    
    # Remove single-character tokens (mostly punctuation)
    words = [word for word in words if len(word) > 1]
    
    # Remove numbers
    words = [word for word in words if not word.isnumeric()]

    # Remove punctuation
    words = [word for word in words if word.isalpha()]

    # Remove stopwords
    #words = [word for word in words if word not in stopwords]
  
    return " ".join(words)

def clean_tweet_segment(text):
    text = re.sub('http[s]?://(?:[a-zA-Z]|[0-9]|[$-_@.&+]|[!*\(\),]|(?:%[0-9a-fA-F][0-9a-fA-F]))+', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub('[\n\r\t]', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub('#\w+', '', text)

    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
        u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons

        u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
        u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)

    text = emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

def clean_text(text):
    text = re.sub('[\n\r\t]', ' ', text)

    words = text.split(" ")
    
    # Remove single-character tokens (mostly punctuation)
    words = [word for word in words if len(word) > 1]
    
    # Remove numbers
    words = [word for word in words if not word.isnumeric()]

    # Remove punctuation
    words = [word for word in words if word.isalpha()]

    stopwords = set(nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english'))
    # Remove stopwords
    words = [word for word in words if word.lower() not in stopwords]

    #Lemmatization
    # words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    
    return " ".join(words)

##########################################################
def clean_text_segment(text):
    text = re.sub('[\n\r\t]', ' ', text)

    text = re.sub(r"[^\w.,!? ]", "", text)

    words = text.split(" ")
    
    # Remove single-character tokens (mostly punctuation)
    # words = [word for word in words if len(word) > 1]
    
    # Remove numbers
    words = [word for word in words if not word.isnumeric()]

    # Remove punctuation
    # words = [word for word in words if word.isalpha()]

    stopwords = set(nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english'))
    # Remove stopwords
    words = [word for word in words if word.lower() not in stopwords]

    #Lemmatization
    # words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    
    return " ".join(words)

def ner_nltk(text):
    entities = []
    for chunk in nltk.ne_chunk(nltk.pos_tag(nltk.word_tokenize(text)), binary=False):
        if hasattr(chunk, 'label') and chunk.label() == 'ORGANIZATION':
            entity = ' '.join(c[0] for c in chunk)
            entities.append(entity)
    return entities

#########################################################
def ner_nltk_location(text):
    entities = []
    for chunk in nltk.ne_chunk(nltk.pos_tag(nltk.word_tokenize(text)), binary=False):
        if hasattr(chunk, 'label') and (chunk.label() == 'GPE' or chunk.label() == 'GSP' or chunk.label() == 'LOCATION'):
            entity = ' '.join(c[0] for c in chunk)
            entities.append(entity)
    return entities

##########################################################
def ner_nltk_segment(text):
    entities = []
    for sent in nltk.sent_tokenize(text):
        for chunk in nltk.ne_chunk(nltk.pos_tag(nltk.word_tokenize(sent)), binary=False):
            if hasattr(chunk, 'label') and chunk.label() == 'ORGANIZATION':
                entity = ' '.join(c[0] for c in chunk)
                entities.append(entity)
    return entities

########################################################
def ner_nltk_location_segment(text):
    entities = []
    for sent in nltk.sent_tokenize(text):
        for chunk in nltk.ne_chunk(nltk.pos_tag(nltk.word_tokenize(sent)), binary=False):
            if hasattr(chunk, 'label') and (chunk.label() == 'GPE' or chunk.label() == 'GSP' or chunk.label() == 'LOCATION'):
                entity = ' '.join(c[0] for c in chunk)
                entities.append(entity)
    return entities

def ner_spacy(text):
    entities = []
    for doc in nlp.pipe([text], disable=["tok2vec", "attribute_ruler", "lemmatizer"]):
        for ent in doc.ents:
            if (ent.label_ == 'ORG'):
                entities.append(ent.text)
    return entities

#############################################################
def ner_spacy_location(text):
    entities = []
    for doc in nlp.pipe([text], disable=["tok2vec", "attribute_ruler", "lemmatizer"]):
        for ent in doc.ents:
            if (ent.label_ == 'GPE') or (ent.label_ == 'LOC') or (ent.label_ == 'FAC'):
                entities.append(ent.text)
    return entities

def label_format(label_value):
    locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, 'en_US.UTF-8')
    return locale.format_string("%d", label_value, grouping=True)

FINAL MODELS¶

1. TWEET DATA¶

SpaCy with sentence segmentation performed the best on tweet data as it provided a good list of companies along with the main company. It similarily performed well for locations.

In [100]:
nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_lg")
tweets_final = tweets_df.copy()
tweets_final['text_cleaned'] = tweets_final['text'].apply(clean_tweet_segment).reset_index(drop=True)
nlp.add_pipe('sentencizer', before='tok2vec')
tweets_final['entities_labels'] = tweets_final['text_cleaned'].parallel_apply(ner_spacy)
tweets_final['entities_labels'] = tweets_final['entities_labels'].parallel_apply(text_lower)
company = tweets_final['entities_labels'].explode().value_counts().reset_index().iloc[0].values[0]
print("The Company name mentioned the most frequently across tweets is " + company)
top_companies = tweets_final['entities_labels'].apply(lambda x: x if len(x)>1 and company in x else pd.NA).dropna().explode().value_counts().reset_index().drop([0], axis=0).head(20)
tweets_final['location'] = tweets_final['text_cleaned'].parallel_apply(ner_spacy_location)
tweets_final['location'] = tweets_final['location'].parallel_apply(text_lower)
top_locations = tweets_final['location'].explode().value_counts().reset_index().head(20)

# Create subplots with 1 row and 2 columns
fig, axs = plt.subplots(ncols=2, figsize=(20,10))

# Plot top 20 companies
sns.barplot(data=top_companies, x='entities_labels', y='index', color='#d11919', ax=axs[0])
axs[0].set_title("TOP 20 COMPANIES MENTIONED FREQUENTLY WITH "+ company.upper(), fontsize=15, loc='center', pad=10)
axs[0].set_xlabel("Company frequency", fontsize=13)
axs[0].set_ylabel("Company name", fontsize=13)
axs[0].tick_params(axis='both', labelsize=11)
axs[0].grid(visible=False)

axs[0].bar_label(axs[0].containers[0], labels=[label_format(x.get_width()) if x.get_width() > 0 else "" for x in axs[0].containers[0]], padding=5, fontsize=8)

# Plot top 20 locations
sns.barplot(data=top_locations, x='location', y='index', color='#d11919', ax=axs[1])
axs[1].set_title("TOP 20 LOCATIONS MENTIONED FREQUENTLY IN TWEETS", fontsize=15, loc='center', pad=10)
axs[1].set_xlabel("Location frequency", fontsize=13)
axs[1].set_ylabel("Location name", fontsize=13)
axs[1].tick_params(axis='both', labelsize=11)
axs[1].grid(visible=False)

axs[1].bar_label(axs[1].containers[0], labels=[label_format(x.get_width()) if x.get_width() > 0 else "" for x in axs[1].containers[0]], padding=5, fontsize=8)

plt.show()

The Company name mentioned the most frequently across tweets is jaguar land rover

3. NEWS DATA - TEXT ONLY¶

SpaCy without sentence segmentation performed the best aa it identified companies and locations most accurately. In fact, this model performed the best across all.

In [102]:
